Senior Advisor to the President and Director of the Office of Intergovernmental Affairs, Tom Perez, recently traveled to the Dominican Republic to continue discussions on economic cooperation, combatting climate change, and addressing the humanitarian and security crisis in Haiti. He was accompanied by Juan Gonz√°lez, Special Assistant to the President and Senior Director for the Western Hemisphere at the National Security Council. During their meeting with President Luis Abinader, Perez reaffirmed the United States' commitment to strengthening regional economic cooperation and recognized the Dominican Republic's leadership in the Americas Partnership for Economic Prosperity initiative. They also discussed international support for the Multinational Security Support Mission to Haiti. Perez held a separate meeting with Labor Minister Luis Miguel de Camps to discuss collaboration on sustainable economic development and opportunities in the Dominican Republic. He also visited a clinic that receives support for HIV response through the U.S. President's Emergency Plan for AIDS Relief. Additionally, Perez met with private sector executives to promote the expansion of the commercial relationship between the United States and the Dominican Republic, and with civil society members to discuss democratic values, human rights, and labor rights.